	   <tr><td colspan=2>My suggestion to level up fast--I went to Lake Of Ill Omen in Kunark at level 14--within 4 weeks of real time I am now level 25 and a half.&nbsp;&nbsp;Get in to a group there and kill off everything in site.  Being as you are Druid, you can bind yourself at the Mill when you reach there--it beats having to run through Firiona Vie everytime.<br>To get to LOIO you need to go to Butcher Block Mountains and run NW--you will come to the shoreline, go right and around the wall--this will take you to the docks.  You want to bind yourself there just in case.  The boat you need is on your far left side.  It is a long ride, but you will arrive in Firiona Vie.  Bind again there.  You will need to SOW and CAMO yourself for the run to LOIO because the Drachs and Frogloks are 35+.  Some of them see INVIS.  Once you zone into LOIO, follow the river until it meets the lake.  Go Left.  Follow the shoreline until you come to Statue pillars and cut through with CAMO on or shout for someone to lead you to the Mill once you zone.  Whichever is easier for you.  I recommend you stock up heavily on food and water and try not to share with anyone, it is a dangerous run to get more--and forage ALOT.  There is no merchant to buy water and food from there, but you can sell to the merchant inside the Mill.  Good Luck and Be Safe!!<br>&nbsp;<br>Kolianu Fyrestorm, Retired member of Vazaelle.</td></tr>
