<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98915476083339></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98915476083339><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98915476083339>RE: Lvl 40, gettin out of hell</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98915476083339#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 6th 9:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Personally, I think Quad kiting can be overrated.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have tried it, and while the immediate xp gain is substantial, so is the downtime.  Personally, I can Root/DoT 3 mobs in the same amount of time it takes me to set up a quad, execute it, and recover.  In fact, sometimes I can get the same amount (4).  *shrug*  I guess it is a matter of play preference.  If you do not mind downtime, quadding is nice.  Otherwise, if you like to keep busy, Root/DoT is the way to go.<br><br>As to soloing in the Dreadlands, don't, at least not right now.  Go back to The Overthere and park yourself towards the SE side of the zone.  No goons to worry about, and most people avoid that area because they think the spawn is a little thin.  OT has a HUGE xp modifier.  I have personally found the DL xp to be horrible =/  Also Drones of Doom* is a tad thin damage wise to use it on some of the DL mobs as your main damage dealer, as it will take forever to kill them if you Root/DoT.<br>*Edited from Drifting Death.  My bad =)<br><br>Just for an example, myself (46 Druid) a twinked to the gills 47 Monk and a 41 Enchanter parked at the Skeleton house.  We had nonstop pulls.  Over the course of 2 and 1/2 hours the amount of xp I got was laughable.  I went back to OT, soloed for 45 minutes, and I had more xp than the previous 2 1/2 hours =(<br><br>At 40, everything should be blue.  I would still avoid the Tigers, Knights, Spiked Succulents, and Stonegazer Cockatrices.  The Berserkers, Thorny Succulents, Stoneleer Cockatrices, Tigresses and Rhinos will be plentiful and an exp cow.  You can even Quad Kite here if that is your desire, just make sure to pull same speed mobs (Sarnaks, Succulents, and Cockatrices are same speed).  Having Terrorize Animal loaded can be nice if you get an add against Rhinos and Cats.  They are also fast enough that if it sticks, they will run out of the aggro range and leave you alone.  You can also fear kite them if you are so inclined, solo or with a partner.<br><br>I did not Quad kite and I still made it out of &gt;45&lt; in less than 12 hours here (have been in OT since 35).  I was grouped to clear 40, and it went very quickly also.  I think once I clear 46, I will move to DL, but not before.  The xp modifier in OT is just too huge not to take advantage.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB (Also did 37 to 45 in OT)<br>Tormada Griffonwing<br>46 Druid BB (No longer the guild port mule)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
