<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98919959990194></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98919959990194><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98919959990194>RE: Lvl 40, gettin out of hell</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98919959990194#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 6th 9:39 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just an FYI, I edited my post to read correctly.&nbsp;&nbsp;Drifting Death should have been Drones of Doom.<br><br>I would personally not use Immolate as a DoT.  If you are FOM, go ahead and throw it on.  The resists get better at about 40 or so, but I found it much easier to just Drones of Doom and med back the mana.  If you want some additional damage, throw a Firestrike instead.  A little more mana for more damage, less resists, and instant gratification.  Remember, it will give the mob a chance to break root.<br><br>The lower blue mobs in OT will take 3 to 4 Drones to force them into flee mode (more often 4).  That is about three maximum duration Ensnaring Roots (level 24 root).  Some people dislike it, but it seems to work OK for me.  1 minute 40 seconds seems to be the max duration I can squeeze out of it, which beats 48 seconds from the other roots IMO.  The level 39 root is a waste during soloing.  If you do not like the level 24 root, go clear back to grasping roots.  Same duration as the 39, just a much lower mana cost.<br><br>Just remember, Tigers, Tigresses, and Rhinos do NOT turn to run when low on health.  It can be a rude suprise the first time if you do not know =)<br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Tormada Griffonwing<br>47 Human Druid <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
