<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9892363339516></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9892363339516><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=9892363339516>RE: Any suggestions?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=9892363339516#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17974><span id=Scholar>mpete</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>217 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 7th 7:52 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.54]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I do not kite using DOT's!!!! I repeat I do not kite using DOT's.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you want to kite then snare your prey, then run outta melee range and blast with your best Direct Damage (DD) spell.  Then stay outta melee range and keep blasting.  You may have to refresh your snare one time.  If you run outta mana before the MOB dies then try either kiting a different MOB or get a partner to hunt with.  Now if you wish to use your DOT then try this.  Snare your MOB, then root your MOB, then apply DOT, then med while the DOT does it's damage.  If the root breaks reapply it, same with snare.  When the DOT wears off reapply it as well.  This way your DOT does full damage.  If you apply your DOT and let the MOB chase you around then the DOT does only 2/3 damage which is actually less efficent than just blasting with a DD.  That's why I say if you want to kite use your best DD.  For the root method use your best DOT and med while it works.  The hardest part of either method is avoiding adds!!  Nothing sux worse than almost having your prey dead only to have a gob or sarnak jump you forcing you to flee without getting your XP and leaving you low on mana (down time!!) sh*t :-(  At lvl 16 I went to The Lake of illomen and grouped at the beach close to the FV zone.  You can solo goblin aggressors and Tigeress at that entrance if you wish.  Loot is soso at illomen at you lvl so if you are in need of plats you may need to kill a few wisps then hit illomen.  Those lvl 19 spells are not cheap!!  Groups are fairly easy to find though and you can solo in illomen so I loved this zone for going from 16-25.  Just one suggestion, I'm sure there are many more.  I really did not like lavastorm very much.  Loot was not good at all and the xp went slow for me.  I only spent from lvl 14-16 there.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
