<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98922337198826></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98922337198826><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98922337198826>RE: Any suggestions?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98922337198826#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=24396><span id= >ailwewen</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 7th 4:16 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First thing to know is that a DOT does only 2/3&nbsp;&nbsp;of the damage if the mob is not standing still or fleeing. Considering this leaves the DOT to be used with decent manaefficiency in grouping (where the mob doesn´t drop in less then a minute), in combination with root or in combination with panic animal. <br><br>How to kite:<br><br>Your spell with the best manaefficiency is dismiss summoned (not sure this is the one, but it is the level 14 vs summoned spell). Untill level 19 where you get careless lightning, the only place to kite is lavastorm. Get inthere, find a lavacrawler, fire imp, firesprite or elemental. ALWAYS have sow, resist fire, skin and coat up. Open your pull with snare. If it gets resisted run towards zone, the mob should be chasing you but can´t keep up with your speed. While running keep hitting your DD or snare, as long as you don´t get the message your target is out of range keep running. When you get the message, stop and cast snare again. Repeat untill snare sticks. When it sticks, run away untill out of casting range. To learn how far this is, use the method with clicking spells while running. As soon as you get enough space between you and the mob hit it with your DD, run again, DD, run, DD untill dead or the mob goes snaredumb (the point where it stops chasing you). When snaredumb you can either DD, DOT or melee till dead. I didn´t melee a lot inthere because a lot of the mobs have a damagshield. A good kite will result in a dead mob that didn´t even touch you once. Hope you find this helpfull.<br><br>level 43 druid<br>level 29 pally<br>Tholuxxe paells<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
