	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well druids are good at soloing but not as good as a bard who knows what he/she is doing. Basically to kite, have sow on yourself, snare the mob, dot, then dd till dead. You can also snare, root, then dot. Coming from playing a bard you'll have to get used to down time, but kiting as a druid shouldn't take as long as with a bard. If you made a halfling give up on the charm, your low cha makes charm pretty much useless. At 16 i didn't bother with charm, i fought in oasis, cast dmg shield on myself, started melee and nuked while swinging, if all else fails you can run and start kiting. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
