	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well I would agree with the other poster about keeping an eye on your primary healer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Make that your #1 priority along with dmg shielding your tank/tanks.  When the primary starts doing there thing MOBs will agro on them.  Your job will be to heal that cleric and use you snare/root to get the MOBS off them if your tanks can't taunt them off.  Then if your cleric is low on mana or worse out of mana you need to take over and heal anyone in need.  Also keep an eye on the other casters, (chanter, mage, wizzy).  Your cleric will likely be concentrating on the tanks so be ready to heal them.  The casters don't have many hp as you well know so ya gotta be ready if they get agro'd.  Hope this helps and good luck!!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
