	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hiya, hope things went well for you:) CC is a greatt dungeon. Sorry its late but here is what I usually try and do in the groups where Im the secondary healer. Usually I will snare, throw damage shield on the tanks, check sow(wont work in CC tho), then med. WATCH THE PRIMARY HEALER:) Gotta make sure your healer stays alive, Then I will watch the others health. I have hot keys set up for standing up (for you I think you would have to make one for /sit off or maybe another command), casting my heal( with a /g healing %t) It kind of depend on when I cast my heals on how quickly your tanks take the damage, if it goes down thru the bubbles fairly slow then 2 bbls health is usually where I start feeling uncomfortable about them, talk this over with your cleric tho, a lot will depend on him. If the Tanks are whackin and the cleric is healin, and everything is going great pop off a dot or dd burn every once in a while, if Im FM i will usually burn 1 bbl mana on that but no more, remember let the tanks firmly get its attention before you burn or the mob is going to be in your face. Always make sure you use the /assist key for tagetting off your main tank to select your targets. If you have a chanter in the group try and get insight as well as clarity, very benificial, NO AoE spells if the Chanter is mezzin or your gonna have pissed off mobs and a pissed off chanter. pay attention to the group leader if he says run ...RUN(and in the correct direction). If you've managed to attract the mobs attention stick close to the tanks, let them taunt it back off you, if you run around this becomes hard for them. Im sure Im missing a multitude of things here but this is all I can think of right now, except have fun:)<br><br>And repeat after me "I am not a tank":)<br><br>Kay<br>&nbsp;<br>Im just here for the beer</td></tr>
