	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think this may be a twofold problem.<br><br>(1) You may be hunting in the wrong places:<br>Personally, I never had problems getting a group in the Overthere up to Level 40 (people started getting "Too High Level-Phobia," which is nonsense).&nbsp;&nbsp;At 40, I've moved to the Dreadlands, along the Karnor Wall, and again have had little problem finding a group.<br><br>(2) You may be never actively starting a group:<br>Once you get some experience in an area, you can organize your own group.  I hunted in OT from 31-40, and I was quite comfortable forming and leading a group after a level or two there.  Take some initiative.  Grab that lone tank looking for work and begin shouting for help.  I guarantee if you're good at your healing duties, the tank will love you.  <br><br>Hope this helps!<br><br>Zephaus<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Zephaus Rootwine<br>54 Druid of Tunare<br>E.Marr<br>-------------------<br>Grandmaster Potter (250)<br>Master Baker (139)<br>Mater Brewer (179)<br>Master Fisherman (180)<br></td></tr>
