<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98890202695995></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98890202695995><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98890202695995>Druid Grouping</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98890202695995#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, May 3rd 11:00 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am new to EQ and have just created my first player, a Wood Elf Druid.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have been reading the various posts on group tactics and have seen some contradictions in the advice (specifically pertaining to DD spells).  I understand that different battles call for different tactics, but are there some things that a druid should just not do in groups?  I melee quite a bit once my mana is low since my heals do not provide much HP yet (I am only lvl 10).  Should I not melee at all?  Is my main purpose to buff?  Do other group members get upset if you sit and med during battle?  Thanks!<br><br>Fairleigh<br>10th Season Druid<br>Fennin Ro<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
