<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98897764526244></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98897764526244><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98897764526244>RE: Druid Grouping</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=98897764526244#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17974><span id=Scholar>mpete</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>217 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 4th 8:00 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>YOU NEED TO MELEE AT YOUR LVL!!!!!!!!!&nbsp;&nbsp;The reason I say this is eventually you will get to a point very soon where you will almost not be able to melee even if you want to.  I'm lvl 31 and many green con MOBs can smack me hard.  The reason you need to melee now is to get you weapons skill, offense skill and most important DEFENSIVE skill up!!  From lvl 1-25 I say melee as much as you can as it will get difficult to impossible later to get your defense up.  Defense only goes up when you are being attacked by a MOB and that MOB has to give you xp or the defense will not go up.  In other words you can't play catchup later fighting a bunch of weak greens!!  If a group has a problem with you going into melee explain to them you really need to raise the above mentioned skills.  If they still have a problem I suggest either finding a new group or go solo.  As for spell choice, if you are the only one in the group who can heal save most if not all mana for that!!  If you have a cleric and you are backup healer then I suggest using you thistle coat to dmg shield your primary tank, snare to stop runners, and root if necessary for crowd control and to protect your cleric.  If the cleric gets low or outta mana then you heal.  Even with a cleric don't go below 50% mana doing other things.  Save that last 50% for emergency crowd control and healing!!  If you have 3 healers in the group and you are not primary or backup healer then you can dmg shield, snare, root, and nuke!!  I actually only grouped about 20% of the time from lvl 1-16.  I chose to solo cause I was already somewhat experienced at EQ and found it annoying to have to constantly teach new people to play over and over.  I also chose to solo allot at these lvls because most of players do not understand we do need to melee a good bit at early levels!!  I take time to check out other class abilities (strengths, weakness, ect) and try to understand why they do what the do.  Many others do not do this!!  There is not really one right answer and this is just one players thoughts on the subject.  So yes you will get conflicting advise at times.  Just read them all and experiment!!  Some experiments will faild miserably and you will think us nuts.  Some will be a smashing success and you may come back and write a thank you message for it.  Just don't be afraid to play around.  Feel free to combind and tweak stratagies.  You may come up with something new and killer to come back and share with us ;-).  So that's all my advise for now.  I hope it will help some.  Good luck and good HUNTING!!!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
