	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well at lvl 10 you will probably need to just heal, 10 is low enough that you don't have a lot of your good spells yet. Personally i would Med if mana isn't full, if it is and nobody needs healed jump in there and melee. I can't remember all the helpful spells at lvl 10 and through those levels i usually try to aviod grouping just to avoid the stress of trying to teach others how to play. If you have snare make sure you snare whatever you are fighting if they run, if you have dmg shield then put that on the main tank. My best advice talk to your group, if they don't have any special requests then try what you want, if it doesn't seem to be that helpful change up and try something else. Most of the time a druids spells will need to change based on the makeup of the group.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
